title: West Zone spikers start with win in all India volleyball meet
text:
NAGPUR: West Zone consisting of city spikers started their campaign on winning note in the 28th Vidya Bharti All India Volleyball Championship which began at the Venus Sports Association ground, Reshimbagh, here on Thursday.
In the girls section, West Zone defeated West Uttar Pradesh 25-9, 25-11 and then downed Rajasthan 25-8, 25-4. West Zone boys dismissed East Uttar Pradesh 25-5, 25-9.
RESULTS
Girls: West Uttar Pradesh bt Central Zone 25-20, 25-20; South Zone bt Rajasthan Zone 25-7, 25-12; West Zone bt West Uttar Pradesh 25-9, 25-11; West Zone bt Rajasthan 25-8 25-4; Central Zone bt Rajasthan 25-21, 25-23; West Zone bt West Uttar Pradesh 25-19, 25-12.
Boys: West Zone bt East Uttar Pradesh 25-5, 25-9; Central Zone bt Rajasthan 25-21, 25-20; Central Zone bt West Uttar Pradesh 25-9, 25-16. Stay updated on the go with Times of India News App. Click here to download it for your device.
